---
description: Code Style
globs: ["*.py", "*.ipynb"]
---

<rule>
name: code_standards
description: Python code style and ML framework usage guidelines
filters:
  - type: file_extension
    pattern: "\\.py$|\\.ipynb$"
  - type: event
    pattern: "file_create|file_modify"

actions:
  - type: require
    message: |
      # Formatting Requirements
      
      1. All Python files must be formatted using the project's autoformat script:
         ```bash
         ./scripts/format-and-run-checks.sh
         ```
         This will run:
         - ruff format for import sorting and code formatting
         
         Configuration is in pyproject.toml:
         - line-length = 120
      
      2. use lowercast types for list, dict, tuple, etc. Avoid 'from typing import List', etc.
      
metadata:
  priority: high
  version: 1.0
</rule> 